<body>

<header>
  <h1>Federation Waystations</h1>
  <p>
    An informational guide provided by the Intergalactic Coffee Federation
    for travelers, traders, and temporary residents.
  </p>
</header>

<section>
  <h2>What Is a Federation Waystation?</h2>
  <p>
    Federation Waystations are neutral locations maintained by the
    Intergalactic Coffee Federation across major transit routes.
    They are not embassies, markets, or cafés, though they may resemble all three.
  </p>
  <p>
    Their primary purpose is stabilization: of travelers, negotiations,
    and interspecies interactions that may be disrupted by fatigue,
    temporal displacement, or sensory overload.
  </p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Core Services Offered</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Palate Recalibration:</strong> Mild, non-reactive coffees designed
      to reset taste perception after long-distance travel.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Context Briefings:</strong> Short, spoken explanations of local
      brewing customs, biological risks, and etiquette.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Neutral Brewing Chambers:</strong> Atmosphere-adjustable spaces
      where multiple species can safely share a preparation ritual.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Archive Access Nodes:</strong> Limited, read-only access to
      the Archive of Grounds for travelers with verified intent.
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Coffee Etiquette for Travelers</h2>
  <p>
    Coffee within a Waystation is never casual. Travelers are expected to
    observe the following guidelines:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Do not consume a brew before its purpose is stated.</li>
    <li>Never alter a shared brew without consent.</li>
    <li>Silence during cooling phases is customary, not mandatory.</li>
    <li>
      Refusing a cup is acceptable. Disrespecting its preparation is not.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="note">
    <strong>Note:</strong> Some Waystations enforce a No-Enhancement Policy.
    Personal stimulants or additives may be confiscated temporarily.
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Common Mistakes First-Time Visitors Make</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Assuming all coffee is safe for all species.</li>
    <li>Requesting specific flavors instead of stating intent.</li>
    <li>Attempting to negotiate before the first sip.</li>
    <li>
      Treating Arbitration Baristas as servers rather than neutral agents.
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Frequently Encountered Coffees</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Transit Neutral:</strong> Extremely mild, used for acclimation.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Stillwake Coffee:</strong> Served to individuals preparing for
      extended focus or testimony.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Mineral Dawn Infusion:</strong> Available only on request and
      only with confirmed biological compatibility.
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Federation Symbols You May See</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>The Spiral Cup:</strong> Indicates a shared brewing space.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Open Kettle Mark:</strong> Signals non-transactional preparation.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Three-Line Glyph:</strong> Arbitration in progress. Interruptions
      discouraged.
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>When Not to Drink</h2>
  <p>
    Travelers are advised not to consume coffee if they are experiencing:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Temporal desynchronization</li>
    <li>Unstable metabolic cycles</li>
    <li>Recent neural augmentation</li>
    <li>Untranslated sensory input</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<footer>
  <p>
    Federation Waystations operate under the Principle of Contextual Brewing.
    Availability of services may vary based on local physics, culture,
    and stellar conditions.
  </p>
  <p>
    This guide is informational and does not replace direct instruction
    from Federation personnel.
  </p>
</footer>

